<TITLE> International conference on medicine begins Sunday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 20 (bdnews24.com)  The International Emergency Medicine Conference, a first in Bangladesh, begins Sunday to share experience, improve relations and expand technological assistance. Over 100 doctors from England, the United States and Canada, for the first time, will attend the conference, Dr. Kazi Mahfuzul Haq, president of United Kingdom-based Bangladesh Medical Association told a news conference Friday. Health minister AFM Ruhul Haq is supposed to inaugurate the conference at the Regency Hotel, while finance minister AMA Muhith attend the closing ceremony Tuesday. Initiated by Bangladesh Medical Association's UK chapter, the three-day conference is held every two years by worldwide emergency physicians. Haq called on private and government doctors to attend the conference to assist new Bangladeshi doctors in the United Kingdom gather knowledge to deliver better service and share ideas. The organisation's former president Dr. M Shawkat Ali said a day-long conference would be held Tuesday, the first day of the conference. In most cases, patients, admitted into the emergency department, die due to weak medication system, he said and added the conference would provide as a platform for sharing knowledge and experience among the practising physicians. Doctors could attend the conference for free, he added. Dr. Badrul Amin Siddiq, general secretary of BMA-UK, former presidents Dr. QA Afsar and Dr. MA Malek, and executive member Dr. Alauddin Ahmed were present at the media conference. bd
